"title": "5468: promises, human",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5468",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Believers must be faithful in keeping promises made to others and to God, because they have been called to live in integrity and truth. False or broken promises are considered as sin.</p>\n<h2>Examples of promises between people</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:22-Gen14:24\">GEN 14:22–14:24</a> <em>Abraham and the king of Sodom</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:22-Gen21:24\">GEN 21:22–21:24</a> <em>Abraham and Abimelech</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen47:29-Gen47:31\">GEN 47:29–47:31</a> <em>Jacob and Joseph</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num30:1-Num30:16\">NUM 30:1–30:16</a> <em>in family life</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh2:12-Josh2:21\">JOS 2:12–2:21</a> <em>Rahab and the spies</em></p>\n<h2>Examples of people making promises to God</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:20-Gen28:21\">GEN 28:20–28:21</a> <em>Jacob</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg11:29-Judg11:40\">JDG 11:29–11:40</a> <em>Jephthah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:11-1Sam1:20\">1SA 1:11–1:20</a> <em>Hannah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam15:7-2Sam15:12\">2SA 15:7–15:12</a> <em>Absalom</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:28-Neh10:29\">NEH 10:28–10:29</a> <em>returning exiles</em></p>\n<h2>Accompaniments to human promises</h2>\n<h3>Taking an oath</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:13\">DEU 6:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:22\">GEN 14:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:24\">GEN 21:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen47:31\">GEN 47:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh2:12-Josh2:14\">JOS 2:12–2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:29\">NEH 10:29</a></p>\n<h3>Declaring a curse</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:35\">2SA 3:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:17\">RUT 1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam14:24\">1SA 14:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:9-2Sam3:10\">2SA 3:9–3:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:23\">1KI 2:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:73-Matt26:75\">MAT 26:73–26:75</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:70-Mark14:72\">MRK 14:70–14:72</a></p>\n<h2>Instructions regarding human promises</h2>\n<h3>The importance of keeping promises</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num30:1-Num30:2\">NUM 30:1–30:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps50:14\">PSA 50:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov5:18-Prov5:23\">PRO 5:18–5:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:14-Mal2:16\">MAL 2:14–2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:4-Matt19:9\">MAT 19:4–19:9</a></p>\n<h3>The sin and peril of false promises</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:12\">LEV 19:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:7\">EXO 20:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:21\">DEU 23:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer8:11-Jer8:12\">JER 8:11–8:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek13:1-Ezek13:7\">EZK 13:1–13:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek13:10-Ezek13:12\">EZK 13:10–13:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech8:17\">ZEC 8:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:17-2Pet2:19\">2PE 2:17–2:19</a></p>\n<h3>The danger of making promises rashly, lightly or in ignorance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:1-Eccl5:7\">ECC 5:1–5:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:25\">PRO 20:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:1-Matt14:11\">MAT 14:1–14:11</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:21-Mark6:28\">MRK 6:21–6:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:16-Matt23:22\">MAT 23:16–23:22</a></p>\n<h2>The call of Jesus Christ to integrity and truth in making promises</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:33-Matt5:37\">MAT 5:33–5:37</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:22-Deut23:23\">DEU 23:22–23:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:2\">ECC 5:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:5\">ECC 5:5</a></p>",
